# Chapolito layout (HTML + stylesheets/all.css)

Use the site's existing layout system. Do not introduce Tailwind, a second global stylesheet, or CSS Grid as the primary page grid.

## Page shell

```html
<div id='main'>
  <div class='identifier-wrapper …'>
    <header class='row'>…</header>
    <main>…</main>
    <footer class='row'>…</footer>
  </div>
</div>
```

Match a sibling page first (case study, `free-design-resources`, or home) before inventing structure.

## Grid

- Container: `.row` (flex, wrap)
- Columns: `.col-{xs|sm|md|lg|xl}-{n}` and `.col-{bp}-offset-{n}` only if defined in `stylesheets/all.css` (~lines 218–613)
- 26-column system; prefer existing column recipes over arbitrary widths or flex hacks

**Canonical content column** (case studies, resources):

```html
<div class='row'>
  <div class='col-xs-offset-2 col-xs-22 col-sm-offset-4 col-sm-18 col-md-offset-6 col-md-14 col-lg-offset-7 col-lg-12'>
    …
  </div>
</div>
```

## Breakpoints (grid class prefixes)

| Prefix | `min-width` | ~px at 16px root |
|--------|-------------|------------------|
| xs | default | all viewports |
| sm | 48em | 768px |
| md | 62em | 992px |
| lg | 75em | 1200px |
| xl | 96em | 1536px |

- **HTML layout:** use `col-{xs|sm|md|lg|xl}-*` — do not assume Bootstrap breakpoints (`xl` here is 96em, not 1200px).
- **New `@media` in `all.css`:** prefer these `em` values when adding layout queries.
- Many case-study blocks also use `px` (`768px`, `992px`, `1200px`, etc.). When editing those sections, match surrounding units; do not convert the whole file in a small change.

## When classes are not enough

- Add scoped rules in `all.css` under `.identifier-wrapper` / page classes (e.g. `.horizon-page__title`), BEM-like naming.
- Use vertical rhythm from existing typography (`1.75rem` line-height, `7rem` section spacing) instead of magic pixel margins.

## Avoid

- Inline `style` for layout/spacing
- Ad-hoc `display:flex` / percentage widths where grid classes exist
- Reading all of `all.css` when grep + a sibling page + lines ~218–613 suffice

**Good:** `.row` + standard content column classes above.

**Bad:** `<div style="display:flex; gap:20px">` or `width: 65%` without grid classes.
